We are given a website to analyze. The index file shows the server source code:
#!/usr/bin/env python3 fromflaskimportFlask, render_template_string, request, Response app=Flask(__name__) @app.route('/') defindex(): returnResponse(open(__file__).read(), mimetype='text/plain') @app.route('/ssti') defssti(): query=request.args['query'] iflen(query) &gt;2: return"Too long!" returnrender_template_string(query) app.run('0.0.0.0', 3002, debug=True) It is a website built with Flask, in Python. One interesting thing is that debug mode is enabled.
The challenge talks about SSTI (Server-Side Template Injection), but we can only enter a 2-byte payload.

